PATCHED version (feature-gated):
```
if (Feature_965997883__private_IsEnabledDeviceUsage()) {  // feature ON
    buf = ExAllocatePoolWithTag(PagedPool, size, 'smtA');
    if (!buf) return 0xc0000017;
    memset(buf, 0, size);   // THE FIX: zero the whole buffer
} else {                    // feature OFF: same as unpatched
    buf = ExAllocatePoolWithTag(PagedPool, size, 'smtA');
    if (!buf) return 0xc0000017;
    // no zeroing
}
// size base for arg5!=NULL is *arg5+0x40 when feature ON, *arg5+0x42 when OFF
```
The zeroing is only delivered when the feature is enabled; the feature-off path retains the original unzeroed allocation.

